The consequences of economic transition have marginalized them and changed their perception of life. The structures for social support in the period of the rapid economic and environmental transition are not yet organized. This is creating the prerequisites for conflicts that still linger in the still unresolved social groups.

The increasing inequality between different groups in the society, social consequences at the workplace, lack of property rights are the main elements of social instability and disagreement. The roots of conflicts can be found in unrealistic expectations that have emerged during the economic transition, in the exchange of encouragement for goals in an unreasonable time and in the society and the specific way (problems) of interpreting various events. The social structure (pyramid), the conditions of political life and the specific effect on the economic structure, the consequences of natural disasters and of the sexual differences are all elements that create a trend of uncertain future and this way within the society.

Increase in the unemployment, which has brought an increasing number of social dependents that require support, can be considered as one of the main factors that create conditions for conflicts and violence in the family. Although the data coming from the interviews show that it’s still considered as the land with the strongest families, particularly the families with 2 or more children, which are adjust to face difficult situations.
